text:
Thought it was good to hear Ryan Tannehill be transparent with his thoughts after difficult offseason. Also believe it'll be good to have a guy like Malik Willis compete/develop behind him. 

I'd rather players be open than criticize them if they don't defer to cliché responses.

text: Ryan Tannehill says he spent time running/throwing this offseason on his own. He's not worried about his contract and believes in his abilities even if others outside the building doubt it. Also says he has no problem with Malik Willis & if he learns from him that'd be great.

text:
Ryan Tannehill was shocked A.J. Brown was traded. Thought a new deal would be done.

Tannehill also said he wasn't informed the team would take Malik Willis, but he texted Willis and 1st round pick Treylon Burks after they were picked. He says his job isn't to mentor Willis.

text: Ryan Tannehill is back at Titans offseason work. He said he missed OTAs to spend time with family in Florida and noted he went to therapy this offseason to get "out of the dark place" he was in after Bengals playoff loss. He says he has deep scars/a lot of sleepless nights.
